        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-12T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="360" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/4–1248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-12T13:00:00-06:00">April 12, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>142. Foreign Minister calling meeting chiefs Mission 2 p. m. indications request
                    intervention Corps. Thanked me efforts <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss>
                    138, April 11, stated events developed to point President believes only
                    alternative house to house defense San José place safety city hands Diplomatic
                        Corps.<note n="1" xml:id="d360fn1">The Costa Rican Government also asked the
                        Diplomatic Corps, if possible, to arrange a settlement of the general
                        political problem; the Corps chose the Papal Nuncio, American, Mexican and
                        Panamanian Ambassadors and the Chilean Chargé (secretary and <hi rend="italic">rapporteur</hi>) to attempt to comply with the
                        Government’s request, according to telegram 143, April 12, 4 p. m., not
                        printed, from Ambassador Davis (818.00/4–1248).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Vanguardia and Calderon factions issuing urgent radio calls all supporters gather
                        <gloss target="#t_CTCR1">CTCR</gloss> headquarters. Just informed Telephone
                    Central taken over by Vanguardia and forcing all politically doubtful operators
                    leave. Fighting apparently progressed from Cartago now at Tres Rios.</p>
                <pb facs="0524" n="508" xml:id="pg_508"/>
                <p>Sent Department 142; repeated Central American Missions. Communication to Limon
                    cut.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
